# Mobile-First UI

## Breakpoints

Mobile-first: base styles for phone, escalate with `min-width`.

```css
/* ❌ BAD — desktop shrink */
@media (max-width: 768px) { .panel { width: 100%; } }

/* ✅ GOOD — mobile escalate */
.panel { width: 100%; }
@media (min-width: 768px) { .panel { max-width: 480px; } }
```

## Touch targets

Minimum **44×44 CSS px**. Minimum **8px** gap between tappable elements.

## Safe areas

Use `env(safe-area-inset-*)` on full-bleed screens. Prefer `100dvh` over `100vh`.

## Interactions

- No hover-only affordances.
- Use `:active` and visible `:focus-visible` for touch and keyboard.

## Layout

- Single-column primary flows on phone.
- Bottom-align primary actions for thumb reach when appropriate.
- Design legible at **375px** width without horizontal scroll.

## Routing

Routes must be deep-linkable URL paths (same paths work in PWA and Capacitor WebView).

See project design docs (e.g. `docs/design/mobile-layout.md`) if present.

Adjust path globs if the frontend directory differs.
